<pb facs="nei.j4c.53.1-2_0001" />

<figure>
<figDesc>Seal of Nebraska's Centennial and photos arragned in the shape of Nebraska</figDesc>
<p><hi rend="caps">SEAL OF NEBRASKA'S CENTENNIAL 1867-1967
CENTENNIAL</hi> 
   <hi rend="italic">Welcome to</hi>
<hi rend="caps">NEBRASKA</hi>land
<hi rend="italic">where the West begins</hi>
1867-1967</p>
</figure>

<note type="clerical">Copied</note>
<opener>
<dateline>
Route 7
Columbia, Mo.
July 1, '67
<note>7-1-'67</note>
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
</opener>
<p>It seems a long while since we exchanged letters. It is probably my fault. I get mixed up in my correspondence.</p>

<p>Since I wrote you last I've been out West &#8212; Eugene, Oregon, San Francisco, Phoenix, Arizona. Had one little adventure. Driving with Mrs Aly to the Eugene airport, <hi rend="underline">we did not stop</hi> at a four-way stop crossing and <hi rend="underline">we got hit</hi>. Nobody hurt this time! (Last time,

<note type="authorial">(over)</note>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.53.1-2_0002"/>

<unclear>you'll</unclear> recall,<del>)</del> it was <hi rend="double underline">I</hi> who got badly walloped). There was some considerable damage to both cars. I missed my plane to <hi rend="caps">S. F.</hi> by 3 minutes. Took another, and very fast, plane in order to catch a plane to Phoenix. Had to wait 4 1/2 hrs. for the plane to be repaired!!</p>

<p>I'm <hi rend="underline">not</hi> encouraged about the <hi rend="underline">biography</hi> &#8212; after about seven years!</p>

<p>I hope you are well. How I wish we could meet at the Bancroft (Neb.) Pageant on Aug. 6th!! We plan to drive up.</p>	

<p>Did I tell you that my <hi rend="underline">The River and</hi> <hi rend="double underline">I</hi> is coming out in the Spring &#8212; in both hard-back<sic>hardback</sic> and paper?</p>
<closer>
<salute>Affectionate thoughts for you and Nita</salute> &#8212;
<signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
